{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a8f73a25-7e0c-40c4-be62-f1bbc33e4031","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Framework Support Dropped in MSTest v3:**\n- ❌ **`netcoreapp3.1`** — no longer supported\n- ❌ **`net5.0`** — no longer supported\n- ✅ **`net462`** — still supported (.NET Framework ≥ 4.6.2 is fine)\n\nMSTest v3 requires **.NET 6.0+** for the .NET Core side. You'll need to update your target frameworks, e.g., replace `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or `net8.0`) and `netcoreapp3.1` → `net6.0`.\n\n**Package consolidation:** MSTest v3 also consolidates `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` into a single **`MSTest`** package, so you can simplify your references.\n\nWould you like me to update the `.csproj` for the migration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f924a869-a059-4b74-8969-2ae4a3c40388","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 has dropped support for some older frameworks. Let me think about what I know:\n\nMSTest v3 (MSTest 3.x) dropped support for:\n- .NET Framework versions older than .NET Framework 4.6.2 — so `net462` should still be supported\n- .NET Core 3.1 — this is no longer supported in MSTest v3\n- .NET 5.0 — this is also no longer supported in MSTest v3\n\nMSTest v3 supports:\n\n\n- .NET Framework 4.6.2+\n- .NET 6.0+\n- .NET 8.0+\n\nSo the user will have compatibility issues with `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1`. Additionally, MSTest v3 consolidated the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages into a single `MSTest` meta-package that includes both the framework and adapter.","outputTokens":573,"requestId":"7032:18DB54:3C97AD:46FD02:69F2BF9A"},"id":"67938e20-5621-42bf-8ff2-1f4046dadc67","timestamp":"2026-04-30T02:34:16.866Z","parentId":"3e425f6a-6f87-4e9d-bda1-99eb13bdef95"}
